# Implementation Plan: Sentinel-1 SAR Water Detection

## Goal Description
Enhance the NovaRisk ESG satellite analytics pipeline by integrating radar-based water detection using Sentinel-1. This multi-sensor fusion approach will combine Sentinel-1 SAR (Synthetic Aperture Radar) with the existing Sentinel-2 optical NDWI methodology to provide a more robust Water Stress Proxy that performs reliably even under cloud cover or during monsoon seasons. The implementation will use `pystac-client`, `stackstac`, and `rasterio` for windowed reads of Microsoft Planetary Computer STAC APIs.

